column5: I got a few pics to share from last fall!  Ive always caught them by accident while fishing for something else. It was the first year that I started to get serious about musky fishing!   This is one I got on a crappie jig on 3lbs line
Yowza, great picture.
Spiel, don't' give Gman too much credit, I've met him and his is only 4'8" tall! ha ha ha
That second pic looks like a Walleye  ........Nice Ski!!  RFS
So he's got a couple inches on you then.
GREAT photographer!!!
I thought it was the way i hold the fish.
This is an older pic but its my PB muskie so far. It measured in at 50 inches

Nice fish everyone, this is great, fish porn for sure.  Here a few of me and the guys up on LOTW last season.  The first 2 are me, I am 6'6" and I hate how small dudes make fish look bigger.  The third pic is of a guy who is like 5'7" with a 4"7, looks bigger than the 49" in the first pic.  The forth one is 46" the guy is also liek maybe 5'7". And the last one is my buddy with a 51", he is about 6'3" 6'4" maybe.            Well just for fun here are some little guys.  I know of quite a few that got caught on LOTW last season, nice to know they are thriving.  The first little stinker was only 20" and hit a 10" Jake being trolled at 4mph, talk about aggressive.  Check out the gorgeous markings on the second one.
My PB - 15 lbs.
My sons first muskie caught in November .. 40" .. his smile says it all
here are a few i've caught over the years.
ooooh fish porn. Sorry, can't participate because of dang dial-up

I will post a couple from my home comp tomorrow, i am working right now at the ol' stud farm. Some beasts there guys.  Anyone wanna give up the location of their catches?
all 4 of the ones i posted are from lake of the woods

I know one of Randy's is from the Allegheny River in Pennsylvania.    Howard Wagener caught it in January, 2002, wading from shore and it very well may have been the Pennsyvania record.   He released it and I know where she swims.
Here's my pb...shes not all that big but it sure is real purtty ta look at!!!

BUSTED  FINALLY!!!!......The second I saw this picture I damn near fell off my chair... I thought I was looking at a picture of myself holding a huge Muskie I didn't remember catching. This guy could pass as my twin!  I've shown this picture to my wife and kids... it fooled them as well as all of my friends...but not my Mother. When I do show it around I usually wait for a few comments and then I fess up." Real fish , real angler just not me"  I'm glad you know where the fish comes from and who the LUCKY Angler was . Thank You!  RFS
Some great fish indeed!  Here's one of my memorables,,,     Cheers G.
